<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF13FF5C8F76FF29" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF13FF5C8AC1FF42" bold="true" box="[151,430,151,177]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species can be separated from the other species by having the superior volsella without setae. The gonostylus has few inner setae confined to the lower half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FF2C8A31FEF1" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" box="[199,350,231,258]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF43FF2C8A69FEF2" bold="true" box="[199,262,231,257]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Male</emphasis>
(n = 1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FEDB8919FEA1" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
Wing length 
<quantity id="181147D4FF39FF60FEE1FEDB8ABAFED9" box="[357,469,272,298]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.67" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="1.67">1.67 mm</quantity>
. Thorax brown, darker at postnotum, scutum, and antepronotum; abdomen pale brown; femur, tibia and tarsi pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FEAB89B3FE39" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF43FEAB8A61FE8A" box="[199,270,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Head.</emphasis>
AR 1.06. Ultimate flagellomere 461 µm long. Temporal setae 9 including 2 inner verticals, 4 outer verticals, and 3 postorbital. Clypeus with 11 setae. Palpomere lengths (in µm): 1st not measurable, 46, 115, 143, 234. Fifth palpomere / third palpomere 2.04.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FE138F0FFE01" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" box="[199,1120,472,498]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF43FE138A4CFE02" box="[199,291,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Thorax.</emphasis>
Acrostichals 13, dorsocentrals 13, prealars 5. 
<taxonomicName id="18E991B2FF39FF60FCC4FE1388D8FE01" box="[832,951,472,498]" class="Trilobita" family="Styginidae" genus="Scutellum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="140" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scutellum</taxonomicName>
with 13 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FDCB895CFD9F" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF43FDCB8A64FDEA" box="[199,267,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Wing.</emphasis>
Anal lobe well developed. VR 1.29. All wing vein with setae except Sc, M, 
<collectingRegion id="1D2D24D3FF39FF60FB00FDCB8FDBFDE9" box="[1156,1204,512,538]" country="Kenya" name="Lamu" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">RM</collectingRegion>
, PCu and An. Wing cell r 
<subScript id="436DE874FF39FF60FF50FDF38B82FDB5" attach="left" box="[212,237,568,582]" fontSize="6" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">4+5</subScript>
apically with few macrotrichia, m 
<subScript id="436DE874FF39FF60FD03FDF389CEFDB5" attach="left" box="[647,673,568,582]" fontSize="6" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">1+2</subScript>
with very few, m 
<subScript id="436DE874FF39FF60FCF0FDF388E1FDB5" attach="left" box="[884,910,568,582]" fontSize="6" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">3+4</subScript>
with about 10 macrotrichia; other cells lack macrotrichia. Squama with 8 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FDB08AF8FCFF" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF43FDB08A69FD67" box="[199,262,635,660]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Legs.</emphasis>
Scale on foretibia 34 µm long, rounded, without apical spur. Spurs on midtibia 34 µm long; on hind tibia 39 µm long. Combs on midtibia both 16 µm long; combs on hind tibia 18 and 23 µm long. Width at apex of foretibia 54 µm; of midtibia 58 µm; of hind tibia 66 µm. Pulvilli as in 
<figureCitation id="47D2F6B4FF39FF60FC70FD018F12FD17" box="[1012,1149,714,740]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="138.[151,254,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[263,1308,210,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-108@138.[226,1360,197,1593]" captionTargetPageId="138" captionText="FIGURE 47. Ainuyusurika tuberculatum (Tokunaga), male (A, E), A. yakucedeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (B–D, F) and A. yakuabeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (G). A, B—hypopygium; C—pulvilli; D—inferior volsella; E, F, G—superior volsella (A &amp; E adapted from Sasa 1988b)." pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Figure 47C</figureCitation>
. Length and proportions of legs as in 
<tableCitation id="926BDF8AFF39FF60FEAFFD398AFCFCFF" box="[299,403,754,780]" captionStart="TABLE 63" captionStartId="140.[151,239,1200,1224]" captionText="TABLE 63. Length (in µm) and proportions of legs of Ainuyusurika yakucedeum (Sasa et Suzuki) comb. n., male (n = 1)." pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Table 63</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FCD08A86FC0F" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF43FCD08A32FCC7" box="[199,349,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="47D2F6B4FF39FF60FEE9FCD18AB6FCC7" box="[365,473,794,820]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="138.[151,254,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[263,1308,210,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-108@138.[226,1360,197,1593]" captionTargetPageId="138" captionText="FIGURE 47. Ainuyusurika tuberculatum (Tokunaga), male (A, E), A. yakucedeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (B–D, F) and A. yakuabeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (G). A, B—hypopygium; C—pulvilli; D—inferior volsella; E, F, G—superior volsella (A &amp; E adapted from Sasa 1988b)." pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Fig. 47B</figureCitation>
). Tergite IX with 8 median setae, laterosternite IX with 2 setae. Anal point 50 µm long, 6 µm wide at base, nearly parallel-sided towards 5 µm wide apex. Transverse sternapodeme 59 µm long. Gonocoxite 174 µm long. Superior volsella (
<figureCitation id="47D2F6B4FF39FF60FD2AFCA18879FC77" box="[686,790,874,900]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="138.[151,254,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[263,1308,210,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-108@138.[226,1360,197,1593]" captionTargetPageId="138" captionText="FIGURE 47. Ainuyusurika tuberculatum (Tokunaga), male (A, E), A. yakucedeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (B–D, F) and A. yakuabeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (G). A, B—hypopygium; C—pulvilli; D—inferior volsella; E, F, G—superior volsella (A &amp; E adapted from Sasa 1988b)." pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Fig. 47F</figureCitation>
) 44 µm long, shaft 11 µm wide, length of T-shape 46 µm, without setae and microtrichia. Inferior volsella (
<figureCitation id="47D2F6B4FF39FF60FC8EFC59881AFC5F" box="[778,885,914,940]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="138.[151,254,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[263,1308,210,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-108@138.[226,1360,197,1593]" captionTargetPageId="138" captionText="FIGURE 47. Ainuyusurika tuberculatum (Tokunaga), male (A, E), A. yakucedeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (B–D, F) and A. yakuabeum (Sasa et Suzuki), male (G). A, B—hypopygium; C—pulvilli; D—inferior volsella; E, F, G—superior volsella (A &amp; E adapted from Sasa 1988b)." pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Fig. 47D</figureCitation>
) 88 µm long, nearly parallel-sided, with 1 caudally directed prominent apical seta. Gonostylus 126 µm long, inner margin setae short, few, not clumped, more in lower half. HR 1.38.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97F3B9BAFF39FF60FF43FBC18FDEFBBC" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF39FF60FF43FBC18FDEFBBC" blockId="140.[151,1436,151,1147]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF39FF60FF43FBC18A2FFBD7" bold="true" box="[199,320,1034,1060]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</emphasis>
Wing membrane with few macrotrichia apically in cells r 
<subScript id="436DE874FF39FF60FB8FFBD08F4CFBDA" attach="left" box="[1035,1059,1051,1065]" fontSize="6" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
4+ 
<quantity id="181147D4FF39FF60FB98FBD08F4CFBDA" box="[1052,1059,1051,1065]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" unit="m" value="5.0">5</quantity>
</subScript>
m 
<subScript id="436DE874FF39FF60FBC2FBD08F30FBDA" attach="left" box="[1094,1119,1051,1065]" fontSize="6" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">1+2</subScript>
and m 
<subScript id="436DE874FF39FF60FB33FBD08FBEFBDA" attach="left" box="[1207,1233,1051,1065]" fontSize="6" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">3+4</subScript>
differs from the description and illustration in 
<bibRefCitation id="BB7897C0FF39FF60FE72FBFE8872FBBC" author="Sasa, M. &amp; Suzuki, H." box="[502,797,1077,1103]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" pagination="53 - 134" refId="ref93638" refString="Sasa, M. &amp; Suzuki, H. (2000 b) Studies on the chironomid species collected on Yakushima Island, southwestern Japan. Tropical Medicine, 42, 53 - 134." type="journal article" year="2000">Sasa and Suzuki (2000b)</bibRefCitation>
. Further, LR 
